<xmi:XMI xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1">
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:ProcessDescription xmi:id="-eGdRcOq80kIEofBdvIZuSA" name="define_business,_yPt68TXDEdq4lJjndbo9Yw" guid="-eGdRcOq80kIEofBdvIZuSA"/>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription xmi:id="-BeEmslWfR-jlD7eavn_oZQ" name="Identify Business Processes,_JnU6kTXEEdq4lJjndbo9Yw" guid="-BeEmslWfR-jlD7eavn_oZQ">
    <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Within the team, you need to come to a common understanding of the boundaries of the organization that you are&#xD;
    describing and decide which processes you will need to describe in more detail.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The purpose of this&amp;nbsp;activity&amp;nbsp;is to:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Decide on terminology.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Identify business goals that support the business strategy.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Outline the business use-case model.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Prioritize which business use cases to describe in detail.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It starts with identifying the current &lt;a class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_goal_D99D08F9.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{6DC6732B-E7F1-495E-B5EC-AEBFD7BE80FE}&quot;>Business Goals&lt;/a>. This is done in parallel to refining the existing &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot; href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_actor_25438422.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{EAD1B7E7-30C9-4494-B369-7F9E16A5329B}&quot;>Business Actors&lt;/a>. &lt;a class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_use_case_14F1BAF2.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{587A849E-B5F2-4B17-8C7F-1C59B0F5612D}&quot;>Business Use Cases&lt;/a> should reflect the target organization. Depending&#xD;
    on the scope of the business-modeling effort defined in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementlink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_vision_55FFBD95.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{C1A31211-2C05-4665-8DC5-6BFB63F4FCE4}&quot;>Business Vision&lt;/a>, the existing business actors and business use cases&#xD;
    might be used as a starting point and refined or completely rethought.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Business use cases are detailed just enough to understand their impact and prioritize them. In practice, a rough&#xD;
    outline of each business use case should be adequate. Where quantitative or qualitative requirements (such as minimum&#xD;
    throughput or adherence to standards) that govern the behavior of the business use cases are uncovered, they must be&#xD;
    documented in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_supplementary_business_specification_BBC64E05.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{0DADA95B-7C1D-44BD-9DB5-41AC99767753}&quot;>&lt;u>Supplementary Business Specifications&lt;/u>&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Commonly used terms and definitions must be captured in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementlink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_glossary_99F5CD1C.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{81F1291A-0FF1-492B-AD0C-10329B75A52F}&quot;>Business Glossary&lt;/a>. Any business rules discovered during this process&#xD;
    must be documented in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_rule_9818835D.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{7F78B340-DD31-451A-9459-25F36E07401C}&quot;>Business Rules&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Based on the business-modeling objectives as defined in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementlink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_vision_55FFBD95.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{C1A31211-2C05-4665-8DC5-6BFB63F4FCE4}&quot;>Business Vision&lt;/a>, the business use cases are prioritized, and the&#xD;
    Business Process View of the &lt;a class=&quot;elementlink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_architecture_document_A73E67D4.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{D3A0CA96-30AD-4461-9386-A3EC9A7E879F}&quot;>Business Architecture Document&lt;/a> is updated with the (adjusted)&#xD;
    architecturally significant business use cases.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;table>&#xD;
    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td class=&quot;copyright&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;table width=&quot;100%&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
                        &lt;tr>&#xD;
                            &lt;td valign=&quot;center&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                                &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.empulsys.com/rupbm&quot;>&lt;img height=&quot;24&quot;&#xD;
                                alt=&quot;Empulsys : software engineering and management&quot; src=&quot;resources/empulsys.gif&quot;&#xD;
                                width=&quot;100&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; />&lt;/a>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                            &lt;td valign=&quot;center&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; width=&quot;86%&quot;>&#xD;
                                &lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot;>&lt;small>&lt;small>This content developed or partially developed by &lt;a&#xD;
                                href=&quot;http://www.empulsys.com/rupbm&quot;>Empulsys BV&lt;/a>.&lt;/small>&lt;/small>&lt;/font>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
                    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
                &lt;/table>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
&lt;/table></mainDescription>
    <keyConsiderations>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Conduct a workshop in which the goal is to decide on terminology and outline the business use cases and business&#xD;
    actors. The following sample techniques can be applied to help you collect the correct and relevant information:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/guidances/guidelines/brainstorming_and_idea_reduction_73112962.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;1.2379282201043798E-305&quot;>Brainstorming and Idea Reduction&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/guidances/guidelines/use-case_workshop_8ED2F80B.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;8.18300315488657E-305&quot;>use-case workshops&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/guidances/guidelines/storyboarding_AD2F0C54.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;8.377275022793495E-305&quot;>Storyboarding&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/guidances/guidelines/role_playing_18BB3ABF.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;2.582376960557169E-305&quot;>role-playing&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></keyConsiderations>
    <purpose>The purpose of this&amp;nbsp;activity&amp;nbsp;is to identify and prioritize business processes that need detailed descriptions.&#xD;
&lt;br /></purpose>
    <howtoStaff>&lt;p>
    Your business-modeling team (all acting as business-process analysts) invites representatives of the stakeholders to
    the modeling effort. This extended business-modeling team must have a strong understanding of how the business
    currently serves its customers and of the direction that the business is taking. The core team needs to have detailed
    knowledge of the business-modeling techniques and good facilitation skills.
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>
    When re-engineering a business, this means that you are effectively deciding who your new customers will be. So the
    individuals who have the power to make such decisions need to take part in this effort, either as active members of the
    modeling team or as stakeholders.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
&lt;/p></howtoStaff>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription xmi:id="-2427oQcxM7A9TabEEqoDcQ" name="Refine Business Process Definitions,_MbENgDXEEdq4lJjndbo9Yw" guid="-2427oQcxM7A9TabEEqoDcQ">
    <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Each business use case will be assigned to a subset of the business-modeling team, who will describe it in detail.&#xD;
    Acting as business designer, this subset team will complete the definition of the business use case and lead a review&#xD;
    session for it. Other members of the business-modeling team are invited to this review session to act as business-model&#xD;
    reviewers. The business designers might also invite representatives of the stakeholders to the project, such as end&#xD;
    users.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The purpose of this&amp;nbsp;activity is to:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Detail the definition of the business use cases.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Describe how the business use cases support the business goals.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Verify that the business use case correctly reflects how business is conducted.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It may be necessary to restructure the &lt;a class=&quot;elementlink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_use_case_model_EC79264C.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{89BEF367-5875-47E0-97D6-23E5BCCE52B8}&quot;>Business Use Case Model&lt;/a> to improve understanding or readability, but&#xD;
    restructuring should not be attempted too early. This is because it is best to wait until the level of understanding of&#xD;
    the business use cases has become sufficient enough to prevent the introduction of unnecessary complexity during&#xD;
    restructuring. Usually, any necessary restructuring should be performed after this activity has been reached.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Depending on the level at which the business use cases have been defined, it may be necessary to &lt;em>refine&lt;/em> them&#xD;
    (&lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot; href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/tasks/refine_business_use_case_13E3A77B.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_NQD5oDOdEduwK5jZAAYgbw&quot;>Task: Refine a Business Use-Case&lt;/a>) so that the refined business use case has a scope&#xD;
    for which it is useful and feasible to specify the flow in detail (and later construct the &lt;em>realization&lt;/em> of that&#xD;
    flow).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Common sub-flows might be identified, as well as relationships between &lt;a class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_use_case_14F1BAF2.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{587A849E-B5F2-4B17-8C7F-1C59B0F5612D}&quot;>business use cases&lt;/a>. Business use cases may also be grouped into&#xD;
    packages. Restructuring should occur only to make the model more understandable or manageable.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Once the &lt;a class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot; href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_use_case_14F1BAF2.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{587A849E-B5F2-4B17-8C7F-1C59B0F5612D}&quot;>business use cases&lt;/a> have become somewhat stabilized, the highest&#xD;
    priority ones must be detailed. This entails further describing each step of the business use case, as well as&#xD;
    completing its remaining properties (preconditions, post-conditions, and special requirements). While detailing the&#xD;
    highest priority business use cases, certain quantitative and qualitative requirements governing their behavior might&#xD;
    be discovered (for example, required turnaround time or process flexibility). If these requirements are applicable to&#xD;
    the business use case only, they should be captured in the Special Requirements property of the business use case.&#xD;
    Otherwise, they should be captured in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementlink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_supplementary_business_specification_BBC64E05.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{0DADA95B-7C1D-44BD-9DB5-41AC99767753}&quot;>Supplementary Business Specification&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The &lt;a class=&quot;elementlink&quot; href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_use_case_model_EC79264C.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{89BEF367-5875-47E0-97D6-23E5BCCE52B8}&quot;>Business Use Case Model&lt;/a> must be reviewed to ensure that it remains&#xD;
    succinct and understandable to all stakeholders. The following must also be reviewed to ensure that the requirements&#xD;
    are clear and realistic: &lt;a class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_supplementary_business_specification_BBC64E05.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{0DADA95B-7C1D-44BD-9DB5-41AC99767753}&quot;>Supplementary Business Specification&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;table>&#xD;
    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td class=&quot;copyright&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;table width=&quot;100%&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
                        &lt;tr>&#xD;
                            &lt;td valign=&quot;center&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                                &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.empulsys.com/rupbm&quot;>&lt;img height=&quot;24&quot;&#xD;
                                alt=&quot;Empulsys : software engineering and management&quot; src=&quot;resources/empulsys.gif&quot;&#xD;
                                width=&quot;100&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; />&lt;/a>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                            &lt;td valign=&quot;center&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; width=&quot;86%&quot;>&#xD;
                                &lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot;>&lt;small>&lt;small>This content developed or partially developed by &lt;a&#xD;
                                href=&quot;http://www.empulsys.com/rupbm&quot;>Empulsys BV&lt;/a>.&lt;/small>&lt;/small>&lt;/font>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
                    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
                &lt;/table>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
&lt;/table></mainDescription>
    <keyConsiderations>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The core development team must conduct a few rounds of internal walkthroughs facilitated by the business designer.&#xD;
    These walkthroughs will clean up any inconsistencies before the work of the core development team is more formally&#xD;
    inspected and reviewed by the extended team.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The team divides the material so that they do not have to review everything at once. The review meeting (covering the&#xD;
    most important business use cases) should not take more than a day.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot; href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/tasks/review_the_business_use_case_model_B683345A.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{9FDA0E91-E5C1-4B4D-A4E6-4CF74655542F}&quot;>Task: Review the Business Use-Case Model&lt;/a> contains checklists that&#xD;
    will be helpful when you are reviewing a business use case.&#xD;
&lt;/p></keyConsiderations>
    <purpose>The purpose of this&amp;nbsp;activity is to detail the business process descriptions and describe how they support the business&#xD;
goals. &lt;br /></purpose>
    <howtoStaff>A person acting as business designer must have strong writing skills. Knowledge of the business domain is, of course, also
helpful, but this can be obtained by involving domain experts as reviewers.</howtoStaff>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription xmi:id="-2cieqVOZnr8utH_QUmWE0Q" name="Design Business Process Realizations,_Y8ixEDXEEdq4lJjndbo9Yw" guid="-2cieqVOZnr8utH_QUmWE0Q">
    <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This&amp;nbsp;activity is the first step toward defining the target &lt;a&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_use_case_realization_55CAF00D.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{47F095EB-E651-4A34-B75B-BACE38ED90C7}&quot; class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot;>Business Use-Case Realizations&lt;/a>. The&#xD;
    current (as-is) business use-case realizations were documented during Describe Current Business. Depending on the scope&#xD;
    of the business-modeling effort defined in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementlink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_vision_55FFBD95.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{C1A31211-2C05-4665-8DC5-6BFB63F4FCE4}&quot;>Business Vision&lt;/a>, the existing business use-case realizations may be&#xD;
    used as a starting point (business process improvement or BPI) or completely reinvented (business process&#xD;
    re-engineering or BPR).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Any terms, concepts, and definitions discovered while performing these activities must be captured in the &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementlink&quot; href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_glossary_99F5CD1C.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{81F1291A-0FF1-492B-AD0C-10329B75A52F}&quot;>Business Glossary&lt;/a>. The business rules governing the current business&#xD;
    use-case realizations may have to be refined. It is also possible that new business rules will be discovered. Business&#xD;
    rules must be captured in &lt;a href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_rule_9818835D.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{7F78B340-DD31-451A-9459-25F36E07401C}&quot; class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot;>Work Product: Business Rules&lt;/a>, either&#xD;
    in document form or as elements in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementlink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_analysis_model_9449F63A.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{CF53445C-3351-46C6-810E-8251830029A7}&quot;>Business Analysis Model&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The architectural views in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementlink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_architecture_document_A73E67D4.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{D3A0CA96-30AD-4461-9386-A3EC9A7E879F}&quot;>Business Architecture Document&lt;/a> should be kept up to date during these&#xD;
    activities. Defining or improving business use-case realizations may raise a number of architectural issues. These&#xD;
    issues need to be investigated, resolved, and described in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementlink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_architecture_document_A73E67D4.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{D3A0CA96-30AD-4461-9386-A3EC9A7E879F}&quot;>Business Architecture Document&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;table>&#xD;
    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td class=&quot;copyright&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;table width=&quot;100%&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
                        &lt;tr>&#xD;
                            &lt;td valign=&quot;center&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                                &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.empulsys.com/rupbm&quot;>&lt;img height=&quot;24&quot;&#xD;
                                alt=&quot;Empulsys : software engineering and management&quot; src=&quot;resources/empulsys.gif&quot;&#xD;
                                width=&quot;100&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; />&lt;/a>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                            &lt;td valign=&quot;center&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; width=&quot;86%&quot;>&#xD;
                                &lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot;>&lt;small>&lt;small>This content developed or partially developed by &lt;a&#xD;
                                href=&quot;http://www.empulsys.com/rupbm&quot;>Empulsys BV&lt;/a>.&lt;/small>&lt;/small>&lt;/font>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
                    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
                &lt;/table>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
&lt;/table></mainDescription>
    <keyConsiderations>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The following sample techniques can be applied in this activity:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/guidances/guidelines/storyboarding_AD2F0C54.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;8.377275022793495E-305&quot;>Storyboarding&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/guidances/guidelines/role_playing_18BB3ABF.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;2.582376960557169E-305&quot;>role-playing&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/guidances/guidelines/business_analysis_modeling_workshop_DB902BB6.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;3.3830970764855035E-305&quot;>Business Analysis Modeling Workshop&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></keyConsiderations>
    <purpose>The purpose of this&amp;nbsp;activity is to identify all roles, products, deliverables, and events in the business, and to&#xD;
describe how the target (to-be) business use-case realizations will be performed by business workers, business&#xD;
systems&amp;nbsp;and business entities. &lt;br /></purpose>
    <howtoStaff>&lt;p>
    This&amp;nbsp;activity is often conducted as a series of workshops attended by the core development team (acting as
    business designers) and some invited domain experts. There must also be at least one person in attendance who has
    previously held the responsibility of business-process analyst to ensure that the business use-case model is
    understandable and to keep the Business Glossary&amp;nbsp;updated. If the business designers lack knowledge in some aspect
    of the business domain, this information can be provided by invited stakeholders.
&lt;/p></howtoStaff>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription xmi:id="-OL9qip24PgO3RcDFykicvw" name="Refine Roles and Responsibilities,_fC32IDXEEdq4lJjndbo9Yw" guid="-OL9qip24PgO3RcDFykicvw">
    <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    In this activity, a number of &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_worker_75AE475B.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{6C6AD4E6-C7B4-42E1-A3D1-FAC9DC2415B5}&quot;>Business Workers&lt;/a>, and &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_entity_638A1D00.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{9A14ED32-2AC5-457E-93B8-474642D33A50}&quot;>Business Entities&lt;/a> are detailed independently. Where changes are made&#xD;
    to the definitions of business workers and business entities, the corresponding &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_use_case_realization_55CAF00D.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{47F095EB-E651-4A34-B75B-BACE38ED90C7}&quot;>Business Use-Case Realizations&lt;/a> may have to be updated to reflect&#xD;
    these changes.&amp;nbsp; The &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_system_BB28EEB.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{4064F184-314B-4965-9F08-6AE5DBF6205A}&quot;>Business Systems&lt;/a> defined in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_architecture_document_A73E67D4.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{D3A0CA96-30AD-4461-9386-A3EC9A7E879F}&quot;>Business Architecture Document&lt;/a> are used to partition the business&#xD;
    workers and business entities. As yet undiscovered &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_event_853992A0.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{EF5798CC-41AE-4137-B248-B308D465CF8A}&quot;>Business Events&lt;/a> may be revealed when detailing the business entities.&#xD;
    The &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_rule_9818835D.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{7F78B340-DD31-451A-9459-25F36E07401C}&quot;>Business Rules&lt;/a> are used when assigning responsibilities to the&#xD;
    business workers.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This&amp;nbsp;activity results in a blueprint for the target (to-be) organization and should therefore be thoroughly&#xD;
    reviewed, especially to ensure that no important architectural issues have been overlooked or remain unaddressed. This&#xD;
    target &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_analysis_model_9449F63A.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{CF53445C-3351-46C6-810E-8251830029A7}&quot;>Business Analysis Model&lt;/a> can be compared to the current (as-is)&#xD;
    Business Analysis Model described during Describe Current Business to assess the necessary organizational changes.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
